# seeder/.env.example
# Copy this file to .env and fill in all values.
#
# Variable types:
#   [BEHAVIOR] Controls how this service behaves. Only this service reads it.
#   [IDENTITY] Credentials or secrets that define who this service is.
#   [SELF]     This service's own address/port. Other services must reference this.
#   [NEIGHBOR] URL or address of another service that this service talks to.
#
# The seeder's own configuration (schools, students, events, etc.) lives in
# variables.py — not here. See variables.py for those settings.
#
# This file only contains the database connection string, which the seeder
# inherits from the backend's app.core.database module.

# [NEIGHBOR] Must match DATABASE_URL in backend/.env and the Postgres credentials
#            in database/.env. The seeder reads and writes directly to this database.
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://<user>:<password>@<host>:5432/fastapi_db
